- **console.log in shared handler:** audit-action.ts line 107 uses console.log directly. Story says \"Do NOT use console.log directly\" but formatAuditHuman() returns pre-formatted strings — wrapping in ok()/info() would double-prefix.\n\n### 3-3-onboard-alias — code-review (2026-03-21T04:38Z)\n\n- **HIGH: Unsafe double type assertion** in audit-action.ts:86 — `as unknown as Record<string, unknown>` bypassed type safety. Fixed with spread operator.\n- **MEDIUM: Dead branch guard** in audit-action.ts:101 — `fixStories &&` always true at that point. Simplified to `else`.\n- **MEDIUM: NFR9 violation** — onboard.test.ts at 325 lines, compacted to 230.\n- **MEDIUM: Branch coverage gap** — missing test for `skipped: true` path. Added, now 100%.\n- **LOW (not fixed): console.log in audit-action.ts:111** — established codebase pattern, needs new `raw()` output utility to fix properly.\n- **LOW (not fixed): formatAuditJson() is pass-through no-op** — exists for symmetry only.\n- **Coverage: 96.97% overall, all 119 files above 80% floor, 2783 tests pass**\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":5,"newStart":1,"newLines":7,"lines":[" # Session Issues Log — 2026-03-21"," ","+---","+"," ### 3-3-onboard-alias — create-story (2026-03-21T04:24Z)"," "," - **Previous sprint file collision:** An existing `3-3-bmad-parser-story-bridge-command.md` exists from a previous sprint's Epic 3. No conflict since new file uses `3-3-onboard-alias.md`."]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
