{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NycCMxz7pzNDTBmgSuKqQz","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story file is ready. Here's the summary:\n\n**Story**: `4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation` at `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation.md`\n\n**What was done**:\n- Auto-discovered story `4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation` as the next backlog story (sprint-status.yaml shows it as `ready-for-dev`)\n- Updated story file status from `backlog` to `ready-for-dev` to match sprint-status.yaml\n- Verified all 10 ACs already had `<!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->` tags -- all correct since every AC can be verified by running unit tests or CLI commands (no workflow, sprint planning, user session, or external system dependencies)\n- Story file already contained full task breakdown, dev notes, architecture references, and verification/testing requirements sections\n\n**No changes to sprint-status.yaml. No git add or commit performed.**\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Problems encountered**: The story file already existed with complete content and verification tags. The `/create-story` skill was not invoked because it would have overwritten existing work. The only actual change needed was a status field update from `backlog` to `ready-for-dev`.\n- **Workarounds applied**: Updated the status field directly via edit rather than running the full `/create-story` workflow, since the story was already fully authored with all sections (ACs, tasks, dev notes, references, verification requirements).\n- **Risks identified**: None. All 10 ACs are straightforward regex-based validation checks that can be verified via unit tests and CLI commands.\n- **Observations**: The epic-4-retrospective.md in this repo is from a *different* Epic 4 (Verification Pipeline & Quality Enforcement from a prior sprint). The current Epic 4 (Infrastructure Guidelines & Validation) is from the oper