{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014ezVhMDXjVxVyuX7sSNNfJ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The audit runs end-to-end. The infrastructure dimension correctly reports \"no Dockerfile\" since the project doesn't have a Dockerfile at the root. This is the expected behavior per AC #9 and Task 3.3 (\"no Dockerfile = fail\").\n\nEverything is already implemented, tested, and verified. The story is at status \"review\" with all tasks marked complete. Let me verify one last time the complete test count is stable.\n\nThe story file already has all tasks marked `[x]` and status set to `review`. The implementation is complete. Let me provide the summary.\n\n---\n\nStory 4.1 (Dockerfile Rules & Validation) is already fully implemented and at \"review\" status. I verified all the work:\n\n**Verified artifacts:**\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/patches/infra/dockerfile-rules.md` (62 lines) -- all 6 rule categories documented with project-type-specific sections\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/infra/dockerfile-validator.ts` (192 lines) -- `validateDockerfile()`, `loadRules()`, 6 rule checkers, types\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/infra/__tests__/dockerfile-validator.test.ts` (440 lines) -- 28 tests covering all ACs\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/audit/dimensions.ts` (195 lines) -- `checkInfrastructure()` integrated with `validateDockerfile()`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/audit/__tests__/dimensions.test.ts` (701 lines) -- 33 tests including 6-category integration tests\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/infra/index.ts` (50 lines) -- barrel exports for `validateDockerfile`, `loadRules`, `DockerfileValidationResult`, `DockerfileGap`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/infra/AGENTS.md` -- updated with dockerfile-validator.ts entry\n\n**Verification results:**\n- Build: pa