{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01L29ZYMVj58MqWKkJPFgRHa","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**Review Complete.**\n\n**Story:** `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation.md`\n**Story Status:** `verifying` (already set)\n**Issues Found:** 1 High, 2 Medium, 3 Low\n**Issues Fixed:** 1 High, 2 Medium\n**Tests:** 2819 pass (0 regressions), 69 in story files (2 new tests added)\n**Coverage:** 96.99% overall, all 120 files above 80% per-file floor\n\n**Changes made:**\n\n1. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/infra/dockerfile-validator.ts` -- Fixed `checkVerificationTools` to use per-line matching with word boundary regex instead of global substring matching. The old code would false-positive when a tool name appeared anywhere in the Dockerfile (e.g., `echo curl`) even if it was never installed, and would also match partial words (e.g., `curlpp` matching `curl`).\n\n2. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/infra/__tests__/dockerfile-validator.test.ts` -- Added 2 new tests: one for tool name appearing in a non-install line (false positive prevention), and one for partial word match like `curlpp` (word boundary validation).\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and fixed:**\n- **HIGH**: `checkVerificationTools` false positive — tool names matched anywhere in Dockerfile content via substring, not on the install line where they should be. `curl` appearing in a comment or echo would satisfy the check. Fixed with per-line matching plus `\\b` word boundary regex.\n- **MEDIUM**: `checkVerificationTools` partial word match — `curlpp` in an `apt-get install` would falsely satisfy the `curl` requirement. Fixed with word boundary regex.\n- **MEDIUM**: Redundant Dockerfile I/O in `checkInfrastructure` — the function read the Dockerfile itself (existsSync, readFileSync, FROM line parsing) before calling `validateDockerfile()` which does the same. Already fixed in a prior session (confirmed clean on current code).\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority):**\n- Test files exceed 300-line NFR9 limit (dockerfile-validator.test.ts: 565 lines, dimensions.test.ts: 697 lines). These are test files, not production source. Would need to split into separate describe-block files to comply strictly.\n- `readFileSync` is still declared in the dimensions.test.ts mock factory (line 6) but never used as a typed mock variable. Harmless but could be removed for clarity.\n- `loadRules()` reads `dockerfile-rules.md` to check existence but doesn't actually parse it — the rules are hardcoded. This is by design (documented in Dev Notes) but means the rules file is pure documentation with no runtime effect. If rules change in the markdown, the validator won't reflect them.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- None below floor. All files at 80%+ per-file. Overall 96.99%.\n- Multi-stage Dockerfiles with multiple FROM statements are tested only for pinned-from checks. The interaction between stage-specific USER/COPY instructions is not tested (e.g., USER only in builder stage, not in final stage).\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None significant. The validator correctly uses the project's `Result<T>` pattern, barrel exports, and < 300 line source files.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed and passing."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ae7c5ce0db996f57c (use SendMessage with to: 'ae7c5ce0db996f57c' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 82829\ntool_uses: 56\nduration_ms: 336137</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"77451c69-f489-4aef-ba6d-37b512cc36ec","uuid":"39f9d599-5f4e-40a8-a9af-8fff927638ad","timestamp":"2026-03-21T05:29:20.716Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixi