ion | Result |\n|----|-------------|--------|\n| 1 | dockerfile-rules.md lists required elements | **PASS** |\n| 2 | Missing binary reports gap | **PASS** |\n| 3 | FROM node:latest reports unpinned | **PASS** |\n| 4 | Passing Dockerfile → infrastructure pass | **PASS** |\n| 5 | Missing verification tool named | **PASS** |\n| 6 | COPY src/ reports source code | **PASS** |\n| 7 | No USER reports gap | **PASS** |\n| 8 | No cache cleanup reports gap | **PASS** |\n| 9 | All 6 categories via audit coordinator | **PASS** |\n| 10 | Missing rules file uses defaults with warning | **PARTIAL PASS** |\n\n**9/10 PASS, 1 PARTIAL.**\n\nAC10 issue: When `patches/infra/dockerfile-rules.md` is absent, validation correctly falls back to hardcoded defaults (all 6 rules still enforced). But the warning message \"dockerfile-rules.md not found -- using defaults\" is never surfaced in either text or JSON CLI output.\n\n**Observability gap:** `codeharness audit` produces no telemetry to VictoriaLogs for any of these interactions.\n\nProof written to `verification/4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation-proof.md`.","stderr":"\nShell cwd was reset to /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
