{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CJMpVXvDmJYDeVStr6wGyy","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 4.1: Dockerfile Rules & Validation — Verification Proof\n     2→\n     3→**Date:** 2026-03-21\n     4→**Verifier:** Black-box CLI verification\n     5→**CLI Version:** codeharness 0.23.1\n     6→**Container:** codeharness-verify\n     7→\n     8→## Setup\n     9→\n    10→Initialized a test Node.js project inside the Docker container with `codeharness init --no-observability`. All verification uses `codeharness audit --json` to exercise Dockerfile validation through the audit coordinator.\n    11→\n    12→```bash\n    13→docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cd /workspace && cat > package.json << EOF\n    14→{ \"name\": \"test-project\", \"version\": \"1.0.0\", \"bin\": { \"test-project\": \"index.js\" } }\n    15→EOF\n    16→codeharness init --no-observability'\n    17→```\n    18→\n    19→```output\n    20→[INFO] Stack detected: Node.js (package.json)\n    21→[INFO] App type: cli\n    22→[OK] Showboat: already installed (v0.4.0)\n    23→[OK] State file: .claude/codeharness.local.md created\n    24→[OK] Documentation: AGENTS.md + docs/ scaffold created\n    25→[OK] Documentation: README.md created\n    26→[OK] Enforcement: frontend:ON database:ON api:ON observability:ON\n    27→[INFO] Harness initialized. Run: codeharness bridge --epics <path>\n    28→```\n    29→\n    30→---\n    31→\n    32→## AC 1: dockerfile-rules.md lists required elements\n    33→\n    34→**Given** `patches/infra/dockerfile-rules.md` exists, **When** read, **Then** it lists required elements: pinned FROM, project binary on PATH, verification tools, no source code, non-root user, cache cleanup.\n    35→\n    36→```bash\n    37→docker exec codeharness-verify cat /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/patches/infra/dockerfile-rules.md\n    38→```\n    39→\n    40→```output\n    41→# Dockerfile Rules\n    42→\n    43→Required elements for verification Dockerfiles. The `validateDockerfile()` function checks all six categories below. Gaps are reported through the audit infrastructure dimension.\n    44→\n    45→## Required Elements\n    46→\n    47→### 1. Pinned FROM Image\n    48→Base images must use a specific version tag or digest. Using `:latest` or omitting a tag results in non-reproducible builds.\n    49→- **Pass:** `FROM node:22-slim`, `FROM python:3.12-slim`, `FROM node@sha256:abc123`\n    50→- **Fail:** `FROM node:latest`, `FROM node`\n    51→\n    52→### 2. Project Binary on PATH\n    53→The container must install the project binary so it is available on PATH. This prevents \"container missing binary\" failures.\n    54→- **Patterns:** `npm install -g`, `pip install`, `COPY --from=builder`\n    55→\n    56→### 3. Verification Tools\n    57→Containers must include tools needed for health checks and diagnostics: `curl`, `jq`.\n    58→- **Install via:** `apt-get install -y curl jq` or `apk add --no-cache curl jq`\n    59→\n    60→### 4. No Source Code COPY\n    61→Containers should use build artifacts, not raw source. Copying source directories inflates image size and leaks code.\n    62→- **Fail patterns:** `COPY src/`, `COPY lib/`, `COPY test/`\n    63→- **Pass:** `COPY --from=builder /app/dist /app/dist`, `COPY dist/ /app/dist/`\n    64→\n    65→### 5. Non-root USER\n    66→Containers must not run as root. Include a `USER` instruction with a non-root user.\n    67→- **Pass:** `USER node`, `USER appuser`, `USER 1001`\n    68→- **Fail:** no `USER` instruction, or only `USER root`\n    69→\n    70→### 6. Cache Cleanup\n    71→Package manager caches must be cleaned to reduce image size.\n    72→- **Patterns:** `rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*`, `npm cache clean --force`, `pip cache purge`\n    73→```\n    74→\n    75→**Result: [PASS]** — All 6 required element categories are documented: pinned FROM, project binary on PATH, verification tools (curl, jq), no source code COPY, non-root USER, cache cleanup.\n    76→\n    77→[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction\n    78→\n    79→---\n    80→\n    81→## AC 2: Dockerfile without project binary reports gap\n    82→\n    83→**Given** a Dockerfile without the project binary installed, **When** `infra.validateDockerfile()` runs, **Then** it reports: \"project binary not installed.\"\n    84→\n    85→```bash\n    86→docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cd /workspace && cat > Dockerfile << EOF\n    87→FROM node:22-slim\n    88→RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y curl jq && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n    89→USER node\n    90→CMD [\"test-project\"]\n    91→EOF\n    92→codeharness audit --json 2>&1'\n    93→```\n    94→\n    95→```output\n    96→{\"dimensions\":{\"infrastructure\":{\"name\":\"infrastructure\",\"status\":\"warn\",\"metric\":\"Dockerfile exists (1 issues)\",\"gaps\":[{\"dimension\":\"infrastructure\",\"description\":\"project binary not installed.\",\"suggestedFix\":\"Add npm install -g, pip install, or COPY --from to install the project binary\"}]}}}\n    97→```\n    98→\n    99→(JSON truncated to infrastructure dimension for brevity)\n   100→\n   101→**Result: [PASS]** — Gap reported: \"project binary not installed.\" with appropriate suggested fix.\n   102→\n   103→[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction\n   104→\n   105→---\n   106→\n   107→## AC 3: Dockerfile with FROM node:latest reports unpinned image\n   108→\n   109→**Given** a Dockerfile with `FROM node:latest`, **When** validated, **Then** it reports: \"unpinned base image -- use specific version.\"\n   110→\n   111→```bash\n   112→docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cd /workspace && cat > Dockerfile << EOF\n   113→FROM node:latest\n   114→RUN npm install -g test-project\n   115→RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y curl jq && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n   116→USER node\n   117→CMD [\"test-project\"]\n   118→EOF\n   119→codeharness audit --json 2>&1'\n   120→```\n   121→\n   122→```output\n   123→{\"dimensions\":{\"infrastructure\":{\"name\":\"infrastructure\",\"status\":\"warn\",\"metric\":\"Dockerfile exists (1 issues)\",\"gaps\":[{\"dimension\":\"infrastructure\",\"description\":\"unpinned base image -- use specific version.\",\"suggestedFix\":\"Pin node:latest to a specific version tag\"}]}}}\n   124→```\n   125→\n   126→(JSON truncated to infrastructure dimension for brevity)\n   127→\n   128→**Result: [PASS]** — Gap reported: \"unpinned base image -- use specific version.\"\n   129→\n   130→[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction\n   131→\n   132→---\n   133→\n   134→## AC 4: Dockerfile passing all rules reports infrastructure pass\n   135→\n   136→**Given** a Dockerfile that passes all rules, **When** validated, **Then** audit reports infrastructure status: pass.\n   137→\n   138→```bash\n   139→docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cd /workspace && cat > Dockerfile << EOF\n   140→FROM node:22-slim\n   141→RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y curl jq && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n   142→RUN npm install -g test-project\n   143→USER node\n   144→CMD [\"test-project\"]\n   145→EOF\n   146→codeharness audit --json 2>&1'\n   147→```\n   148→\n   149→```output\n   150→{\"dimensions\":{\"infrastructure\":{\"name\":\"infrastructure\",\"status\":\"pass\",\"metric\":\"Dockerfile valid\",\"gaps\":[]}}}\n   151→```\n   152→\n   153→(JSON truncated to infrastructure dimension for brevity)\n   154→\n   155→**Result: [PASS]** — Infrastructure status is \"pass\" with zero gaps and metric \"Dockerfile valid\".\n   156→\n   157→[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction\n   158→\n   159→---\n   160→\n   161→## AC 5: Missing verification tool reports gap naming the tool\n   162→\n   163→**Given** `patches/infra/dockerfile-rules.md` defines required verification tools (curl, jq), **When** a Dockerfile is missing one of these tools, **Then** `validateDockerfile()` reports a gap naming the missing tool.\n   164→\n   165→```bash\n   166→docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cd /workspace && cat > Dockerfile << EOF\n   167→FROM node:22-slim\n   168→RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y jq && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n   169→RUN npm install -g test-project\n   170→USER node\n   171→CMD [\"test-project\"]\n   172→EOF\n   173→codeharness audit --json 2>&1'\n   174→```\n   175→\n   176→```output\n   177→{\"dimensions\":{\"infrastructure\":{\"name\":\"infrastructure\",\"status\":\"warn\",\"metric\":\"Dockerfile exists (1 issues)\",\"gaps\":[{\"dimension\":\"infrastructure\",\"description\":\"verification tool missing: curl\",\"suggestedFix\":\"Install curl via apt-get install or apk add\"}]}}}\n   178→```\n   179→\n   180→(JSON truncated to infrastructure dimension for brevity)\n   181→\n   182→**Result: [PASS]** — Gap reported: \"verification tool missing: curl\" — names the specific missing tool.\n   183→\n   184→[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction\n   185→\n   186→---\n   187→\n   188→## AC 6: COPY src/ reports source code in container\n   189→\n   190→**Given** a Dockerfile with `COPY src/ /app/src/`, **When** validated, **Then** it reports: \"source code copied into container -- use build artifact instead.\"\n   191→\n   192→```bash\n   193→docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cd /workspace && cat > Dockerfile << EOF\n   194→FROM node:22-slim\n   195→COPY src/ /app/src/\n   196→RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y curl jq && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n   197→RUN npm install -g test-project\n   198→USER node\n   199→CMD [\"test-project\"]\n   200→EOF\n   201→codeharness audit --json 2>&1'\n   202→```\n   203→\n   204→```output\n   205→{\"dimensions\":{\"infrastructure\":{\"name\":\"infrastructure\",\"status\":\"warn\",\"metric\":\"Dockerfile exists (1 issues)\",\"gaps\":[{\"dimension\":\"infrastructure\",\"description\":\"source code copied into container -- use build artifact instead.\",\"suggestedFix\":\"Use COPY --from=bu