 maps it to a gap. But the metric says \"7 issues\" which means `gaps.length` = 7 at that point. The warnings gap is pushed after the validation gaps... wait, `result.data.gaps` has the 7 validation gaps, and `result.data.warnings` has 1 warning, so total gaps should be 8.\n\nLet me test this locally."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3729,"cache_read_input_tokens":68573,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3729},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"77451c69-f489-4aef-ba6d-37b512cc36ec","uuid":"a599d592-7c37-41f5-88b8-bafb55d57021"}
