 is **not surfaced** in either the text or JSON output.\n   342→\n   343→**Result: [PARTIAL PASS]** — Hardcoded defaults work correctly (all 6 rules enforced without the rules file). But the AC-specified warning message \"dockerfile-rules.md not found -- using defaults\" is not visible in CLI output. The warning may be emitted internally but is not propagated to the user-facing audit output.\n   344→\n   345→[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction\n   346→\n   347→---\n   348→\n   349→## Summary\n   350→\n   351→| AC | Description | Result |\n   352→|----|-------------|--------|\n   353→| 1 | dockerfile-rules.md lists required elements | **PASS** |\n   354→| 2 | Missing binary reports gap | **PASS** |\n   355→| 3 | FROM node:latest reports unpinned | **PASS** |\n   356→| 4 | Passing Dockerfile → infrastructure pass | **PASS** |\n   357→| 5 | Missing verification tool named | **PASS** |\n   358→| 6 | COPY src/ reports source code | **PASS** |\n   359→| 7 | No USER reports gap | **PASS** |\n   360→| 8 | No cache cleanup reports gap | **PASS** |\n   361→| 9 | All 6 categories via audit coordinator | **PASS** |\n   362→| 10 | Missing rules file uses defaults with warning | **PARTIAL PASS** |\n   363→\n   364→**Overall: 9/10 PASS, 1 PARTIAL**\n   365→\n   366→AC10 partial: defaults work, but the warning message is not user-visible.\n   367→\n   368→**Observability:** No log events were detected for any audit interaction. The audit command does not emit telemetry to VictoriaLogs. This is a systemic observability gap across all ACs.\n   369→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"77451c69-f489-4aef-ba6d-37b512cc36ec","uuid":"cd134675-bc60-4383-940c-701bc7a97644","timestamp":"2026-03-21T05:38:35.409Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/verification/4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation-proof.md","content":"## AC 10: Missing dockerfile-rules.md uses defaults with warning\n\n**Given** no `pa